            <b>Baggage Policy</b></br>At Road Runners, we want to make your travel experience as comfortable as possible. We allow each passenger to bring one carry-on bag and one personal item, such as a purse or laptop bag, on board free of charge.</br>Your carry-on bag must fit in the overhead compartment or under the seat in front of you, and must not exceed the following dimensions: 22 x 14 x 9 inches (56 x 36 x 23 cm). Your personal item must fit under the seat in front of you and should not exceed the dimensions of 18 x 14 x 8 inches (46 x 36 x 20 cm).</br>brFor checked baggage, we allow up to two pieces of luggage per passenger, with a maximum weight of 50 pounds (23 kg) per bag. Any additional bags or bags exceeding the weight limit may be subject to additional fees.</br>Certain items are not allowed on board, such as hazardous materials, explosives, or live animals (with the exception of service animals). If you have any questions about our baggage policy or the items you can bring on board, please contact our customer support team.</br>
